<h1>MacBook Problems and How They Are Diagnosed</h1>

<p class="lead">When a MacBook stops working properly, the first instinct is usually to search for the symptom: "MacBook won't turn on," "MacBook screen flickering," or "MacBook running slow." But here's what we've learned after years of repairing Macs in the Hills District—the symptom you're seeing is rarely the full picture, and the obvious cause is often wrong.</p>

<p>This guide exists to help you understand how MacBook problems actually work. Not just what might be wrong, but why so many issues get misdiagnosed, why symptoms overlap, and when you genuinely need professional repair versus when a simple fix at home will solve it.</p>

